                  <provenance notBefore="1502"><orgName role="fmo" key="org_133214228">Eberbach, Cistercian abbey</orgName>: almost certainly identifiable from contents as g 15 in the catalogue of 1502 ('sermones de quatuor fluminibus paradisi Initium Columbarum': N. Palmer, <title>Zisterzienser und ihre Bücher: die mittelalterliche Bibliotheksgeschichte von Kloster Eberbach im Rheingau</title> (Regensburg, 1998), p. 273, but not mentioning the present manuscript).</provenance>
                  <provenance when="1638"><persName role="fmo" key="person_54940373">William Laud, 1573–1645</persName>: ex-libris inscription of Archbp. Laud, dated 1638, at the lower margin of fol. 1r. Acquired after the dissolution of the Eberbach library in the period of the Thirty Years' War.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1639">Given to the Bodleian as part of his third donation, dispatched on 28 June 1639.</acquisition>
